meta.description: Comprehensive prompt compression dictionary for AI image generation platforms

fillers.description: Zero semantic value words - always remove regardless of platform

redundancy.description: Patterns where one word implies the other - remove redundant term

style.description: Art style and rendering technique compressions

camera.description: Camera angles, shots, and composition terms

negativeToPositive.description: Convert negative prompts to positive equivalents for natural language platforms

sdWeighted.description: Stable Diffusion weight syntax compressions (Tier 1 CLIP-based only)
sdWeighted.note: These apply CLIP weight emphasis syntax for SD-family platforms

midjourneySpecific.note: These apply Midjourney weight and parameter syntax

booruTags.description: NovelAI and anime booru tag compressions (Tier 1 CLIP-based, anime models)
booruTags.note: Common booru/danbooru tags for anime-style platforms like NovelAI

abbreviations.description: Standard abbreviations that AI models understand - tier-specific support
abbreviations.note: These abbreviations save characters while maintaining meaning. Tier 1-2 support most, Tier 3-4 only universal.

tier3.description: Universal abbreviations only (8K, 4K, HD, 3D, UHD) - natural language platforms may not understand technical shorthand
tier3.note: These platforms use natural language processing. Only universally understood abbreviations.

tier4.note: Consumer platforms - only universally understood terms. Prefer spelled out.

redundantModifiers.description: Intensity modifiers that add length but not semantic value
redundantModifiers.note: These modifiers inflate prompts without improving output. Safe to strip across all tiers.

impliedTerms.description: Terms that AI models assume by default - removing saves space without quality loss
impliedTerms.note: Research shows these terms are redundant as models already optimize for them

tier1and2.description: Terms implied by CLIP-based and Midjourney platforms

tier3and4.description: More conservative for natural language platforms
tier3and4.note: Natural language models may use these as guidance, so be more conservative

negativeConsolidation.description: Consolidate multiple negative terms for Midjourney family
negativeConsolidation.note: MJ supports comma/slash in --no section. Consolidation saves chars.

progressiveShedding.description: Remove low-value adjectives when multiple modifiers present. Keeps most specific/impactful words.
progressiveShedding.note: Applies when 3+ adjectives modify a single noun. Removes generic/weak adjectives first.
